  <article id="comment-1055433" class="single-comment">
    <div>
      <header>
        <div>
                      <a href="/users/nikkomann/comments" title="View Nikkomann&#039;s profile">Nikkomann</a>                                <time class="created" title="2011-09-27T03:52:15+00:00">Sep 27th 2011 3:52 GMT</time>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="comment-body"><p>This is a very ingenious idea and can possibly have great potential.  There are some things to take into account though such as the dangers of having drivers focus more on cellphones and not the road.  This system also physically affects other people yet it relies on an individual's cellphone which can be buggy due to experimentation by the user.  A faulty phone can distract the driver much more than wanted posing safety concerns.  While this has great potential I believe that work into an adapting traffic grid system would be better.  It is more exclusive and does not rely on the public for information which could be susceptible to error.</p>
</div>
