  <article id="comment-1055005" class="single-comment">
    <div>
      <header>
        <div>
                      <a href="/users/905619795/comments" title="View 905619795&#039;s profile">905619795</a>                                <time class="created" title="2011-09-26T21:44:17+00:00">Sep 26th 2011 21:44 GMT</time>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="comment-body"><p>For most, approaching a stoplight is somewhat of a burden. Whether the driver is limited on time or thinking about the cost of fuel, the anticipation of the light turning red is a frustrating event. Not only does it waste time, but it also burns fuel, which essentially burns cash. However, the invention of the SignalGuru will lessen the likelihood of the public having to wait on a red light to change by suggesting the speed at which the driver should travel. This in turn will cut fuel consumption down by 20%. Therefore, the invention is a cheaper and more effective way of life for society.</p>
</div>
