  <article id="comment-1044886" class="single-comment">
    <div>
      <header>
        <div>
                      <a href="/users/ebnerseb/comments" title="View ebnerseb&#039;s profile">ebnerseb</a>                                <time class="created" title="2011-09-20T01:54:22+00:00">Sep 20th 2011 1:54 GMT</time>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="comment-body"><p>Its good to know that today Mobile Apps are beeing used not only to increase fuel consumtion(like the g-force-meter) but even lower it and so help to clean up the energy.<br />
By the way:<br />
The first technique trying to improve fuel consumtion was done in Russia: There in many cities you can see light signs over the traffic lights showing how long the lights stay green and also how long they will stay red.<br />
This then was developed by different car producers like toyota and bmw, who tried to install a system into every car, communicating with the ones around(like the app is doing now!)-their problem was to find a basis, on which this should work(like radiocommunication or the internet).<br />
So you see:<br />
Steve did his job!</p>
</div>
