  <article id="comment-1044483" class="single-comment">
    <div>
      <header>
        <div>
                      <a href="/users/lauren8/comments" title="View lauren8&#039;s profile">lauren8</a>                                <time class="created" title="2011-09-19T20:45:03+00:00">Sep 19th 2011 20:45 GMT</time>
        </div>
      </header>
      <div class="comment-body"><p>This is a great idea, but it isn't practical. Using this might save you a few extra dollars in gas, but it won't save your life. In fact, it probably will increase your chances of getting into a crash. How can you focus on getting the phone's camera positioned and ready while also driving at the same time? It would also kill your phone's battery if you used this all the time. </p>
<p>The concept should be applied into a car's navigation system. That way, it could automatically detect the stoplights and send data to other users. The data could then be transmitted into your car's speakers, so you can just listen to find out the optimal speed, without having to fumble around with the phone itself.</p>
</div>
      <footer class="clearfix">
                  <ul class="links"><li class="comment_recommend first"><a href="/vote/recommend-comment/1044483?token=65a845a1e70854bb9a5ff1f416038080&amp;nid=21528910&amp;page=0&amp;sort=0" title="Recommend comment: This is a great idea, but it" class="recommend" data-ec-omniture="recommend_comment" rel="nofollow">Recommend</a> <div><span>7</span></div></li>
