<li><a href="/blogs/leviathan" title="In this blog, our public policy editor reports on how governments in Britain and beyond are rethinking and reforming the state&#039;s role in public services, the arts and life in general. The blog takes its name from Thomas Hobbes&#039;s book of 1651, which remains one of the most influential examinations of the relationship between government and society.
">Leviathan<span class="description"> | Public policy</span></a></li>
